{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c9916201-abef-4af0-99a9-f4af52a2021b","content":"I can help guide you on analyzing your .dmp file! Note: the `dump-collect` skill I have available is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them.\n\nHere are the main tools for .NET crash dump analysis:\n\n### `dotnet-dump analyze`\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect specific threads\n\n### LLDB (Linux)\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nsos clrstack\nsos pe\n```\n\n### Visual Studio / WinDbg (Windows)\nOpen the `.dmp` directly in VS or WinDbg for a visual debugging experience.\n\n---\n\n**Quick triage steps:**\n1. Run `pe` to check for an unhandled exception\n2. Run `threads` → find the faulting thread\n3. Run `clrstack` on that thread to see where it crashed\n\nWant me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file if it's accessible in this environment?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"beca31e4-8185-4242-b164-93d3bf9cc78a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for configuring and collecting crash dumps, and explicitly states \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":433,"requestId":"1B86:2BCA1C:16E2175:199E478:6A02886B"},"id":"0c13d5f5-224e-4295-aa94-ec87ebe5fe41","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:55:04.207Z","parentId":"e92c2de7-5aa1-49e7-abe9-9b5f2704faf6"}
